                    <span>The author provides broad overview of the semantic web and XML. It gives a beginner some insights into the field. It does not go into depth on XML, but gives several references for the reader to find more information. It also takes a database perspective in discussing the semantic web rather than an artificial intelligence perspective. I find this aspect very interesting.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very Interesting Book</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
